<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Measures 1, 3, 9, 18: D root position open (D-A-D-F# in LH). Standard "33" pattern.
- Measure 3, 12: Arpeggio "movement" in RH while LH sustains — rhythmic variety.
- Measures 5, 10: Bm with open 5th spacing (B-F#-B) in LH.
- Measure 8: Fast chord changes (Em-D-Em7-Bm), each beat gets its chord — rich harmonic rhythm.
- Measure 12: A major ascending arpeg in RH (A-C#-E-C#) — climax approach.
- Measure 15: Sus4 suspension (A sus4 → A) for expressive cadence color.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Measure 7: All four beats change chord; RH voice-leads stepwise C#→D→C#→F#, smooth.
- Measure 8: Contrary motion — RH rises E→D→G→F# while LH descends E→D→E→B.
- Measure 17: Em7→Em collapse in final phrase provides smooth inner voice resolution.

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1-3: Sparse opening (2-voice RH, 3-note LH), D tonic establishes.
- mm. 4-6: Bm/A/D center; LH gains 4th note in key moments.
- mm. 7-9: Phrase cadence with active chord rhythms, full 4-note LH at climax of phrase.
- mm. 10-12: Second phrase, F#m/G color adds richness; RH arpeg in m12.
- mm. 13-15: Sus4 suspension at cadence; RH gains 3rd note.
- mm. 16-18: Full four-chord m16 as climax; convergent whole-note final D cadence.
-->
